parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning airbag warning light can lead to a false sense of security, potentially causing serious injury or death if the airbag fails to deploy in an accident. The constant flashing of the light can also be a distraction while driving, especially at night.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on or flashes continuously
indicating a potential problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can prevent the airbag from deploying in an accident, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on or flashes
indicating a problem with the airbag sensor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in an accident can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag fails to deploy in an accident
despite the presence of an airbag warning light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause a fire, which can lead to a vehicle fire, damage to the vehicle, and potentially harm the occupants or bystanders.
symptoms: Smoke emitting from the hood
high-pitched noise while idling
orange flames visible in the alternator area
smoke flowing out of the grill area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system, specifically the alternator, generator, or regulator, can cause a fire, which can lead to a vehicle fire, damage to the vehicle, and potentially harm the occupants or bystanders.
symptoms: Smoke emitting from the hood
high-pitched noise while idling
orange flames visible in the alternator area
smoke flowing out of the grill area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system contamination can cause severe engine problems, including rough idling, fuel odor, and smoke emission, which can lead to engine failure, decreased performance, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Rough idling
fuel odor
blue-black smoke emission from the exhaust pipe
check engine light illumination
gas fumes collecting and seeping into the passenger cabin
fuel pump shutting off when filling the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel injector failure can cause engine performance issues, including rough idling, misfires, and decreased fuel efficiency, which can lead to engine failure and decreased safety.
symptoms: Rough idling
engine misfires
decreased fuel efficiency
fuel odor
blue-black smoke emission from the exhaust pipe
metal shavings found on the fuel injector.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Evaporative emission system failure can cause fuel vapors to leak into the passenger cabin, creating a hazardous environment for occupants and potentially leading to engine performance issues.
symptoms: Gas fumes collecting and seeping into the passenger cabin
fuel odor
check engine light illumination
fuel pump shutting off when filling the tank.
